Updated the block light in the cuboid from %s %s %s to %s %s %s, including %s blocks in total
commands.mishanguc:update-light.warn_not: The light update command is not stable. It may cause differences between client and server. You can exit and re-join the world to confirm the light update.
commands.mishanguc:update-light.mass: You are updating a large area of light, which may cause lag of server. If the server does not respond, please wait in patient. You will be informed when the process finished.
commands.mishanguc:update-light.to_big: The range in which to update block light is to big (%2$s > %1$s)!
commands.mishanguc:update-light.descript: This command is used to update the block light for a single pos, or in a range of a cuboid. The syntax of the command is as follows:
Update light for a single position. If the position is not provided, the execution position will be used.

Update light for a range of a center within a specified range. The range cannot be larger than %1$s. Numbers of blocks affected will be (2 * %2$s + 1)³. If the center pos is not provided, the execution position will be used.
Update light for a cuboid range determined by two positions. Numbers of blocks in this range cannot be larger than %1$s.

If the command contains a huge range, it may cause your server to lag, freeze, or even run out of memory. Therefore, to update light for a huge region, it is recommended to divide it into segments, and execute this command for them respectively. The command after execution will sync the updates to client, but it is not stable. You can quit and re-join the world to confirm the light update has been finished.
